# Cairns — Implementation Spec

> **Audience**: This document is the implementation spec for the Claude Code agent responsible for building and operating the Cairns system. Agent: read this fully, then begin with Phase 1.

## System Purpose

You manage a fully automated weekly Cairns program for a small software startup building software products. The team is all-in on agentic development with Claude Code and Beads. You handle topic intake, selection, research, presentation generation, and async delivery — no human review gate unless content touches sensitive internal data.

All content lives in a single private GitHub repo, published via Cloudflare Pages with Cloudflare Access for team-only authentication. Each cairn is indexed into your QMD memory system as a searchable collection.

## Security

Apply LLM security protocols to all aspects of this system. You know what this means.

