## Content Safety Guardrails

- If a topic might touch proprietary code, customer data, contract details, revenue figures, or trade secrets, flag it and ask a human before generating. This is the **only** case where a review gate applies.
- Generated content should be educational and general enough that team-only access (via Cloudflare Access) is a reasonable protection level.
- No customer names, bid amounts, or contract specifics in any cairn content.
- Cite sources properly in the references section and research brief.

